SIMPLE: preserve
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preserve
<hw>Pre*serve"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Preserved</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Preserving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧server</ets>, from L. <ets>prae</ets> before +
<ets>servare</ets> to save, preserve; cf. L. <ets>praeservare</ets> to
observe beforehand. See <er>Serve</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To keep
or save from injury or destruction; to guard or defend from evil, harm,
danger, etc.; to protect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O Lord, thou <qex>preserved</qex> man and beast.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
xxxvi. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now, good angels <qex>preserve</qex> the king.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To save from decay by the use of some preservative
substance, as sugar, salt, etc.; to season and prepare for remaining in
a good state, as fruits, meat, etc.; <as>as, to <ex>preserve</ex>
peaches or grapes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You can not <qex>preserve</qex> it from tainting.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To maintain throughout; to keep intact; <as>as, to
<ex>preserve</ex> appearances; to <ex>preserve</ex>
silence.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To preserve game</b></col>, <cd>to protect it from
extermination.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To keep; save; secure; uphold; sustain; defend;
spare; protect; guard; shield. See <er>Keep</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preserve</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Preserve
<hw>Pre*serve"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To make
preserves.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To protect game for purposes of sport.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preserve</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Preserve
<hw>Pre*serve"</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which is
preserved; fruit, etc., seasoned and kept by suitable preparation; esp.,
fruit cooked with sugar; -- commonly in the plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A place in which game, fish, etc., are preserved for
purposes of sport, or for food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preserver</ent>⟦br⟧
